Additionally, you have the right to lodge a complaint against us. To do so, contact the supervisory authority in your country of residence.
International Data Transfers
- If you are visiting the Sites from outside the United States, please be aware that the Personal Data we collect may be transferred to and maintained on servers or databases located outside your jurisdiction, including the United States. These locations may not necessarily have data protection laws as comprehensive or protective as those in your country of residence. In some instances, we rely on the Standard Contractual Clauses with data processors to legitimize data transfers to the United States.
CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS
California residents have certain rights under the California Consumer Privacy Act with respect to Personal Data we collect. If you are a resident of California, this section of the Privacy Policy contains disclosures required by law and explains rights that may be available to you.
Personal Information We Collect and Disclose
- In the preceding 12 months, we collected and disclosed the following categories of Personal Data:
Personal and online identifiers (such as first and last name, email address, physical address, or unique online identifiers);
Recordkeeping information (such as physical characteristics or description, credit card number, debit card number, or health information);
Characteristics of legally protected classifications (such as gender);
Commercial or transactions information (such as records of products or services purchased, obtained, or considered);
Internet or other electronic network activity information (such as browsing history, search history, interactions with a website, email, application, or advertisement);
Geolocation information;
Sensory information (such as your photograph);
Professional or employment-related information;
Inferences drawn from the above information about your predicted characteristics and preferences; and
Other information about you that is linked to the Personal Data above.
We share Personal Data for cross-context behavioral advertising purposes but do not otherwise engage in “sales” of Personal Data as defined by state laws. Additionally, we do not knowingly sell or share Personal Data of individuals under sixteen (16) years of age.
Some of the information described above may be considered “sensitive personal information” under the CCPA. We do not use or disclose sensitive personal information for purposes other than those specified in the CCPA.
