DIGITAL ADVERTISING & ANALYTICS
We may partner with ad network and other ad serving providers (“Advertising Providers”) to serve ads on our behalf on non-affiliated third-party websites. Some of those ads may be personalized, meaning that they are intended to be relevant to you based on information we or the online advertising network serving the ad collect about your use of the Sites and other sites and apps over time, including information about relationships among different browsers and devices. This type of advertising is known as interest-based advertising.
You may visit the Network Advertising Initiative at
https://www.networkadvertising.org/managing/opt_out.asp
and the Digital Advertising Alliance (“DAA”) at
https://www.aboutads.info/consumers/
for information about this type of advertising and how to opt-out of this advertising on websites by companies participating in their programs. You can also exercise choices regarding interest-based advertising on your mobile device by downloading the appropriate version of the DAA's AppChoices tool at
https://youradchoices.com/appchoices
. If you delete your cookies or use a different browser or mobile device, you may need to renew your opt-out choices exercised through the opt-out tools. Note that if you opt-out of these types of ads, you will still see ads in your browser or application. It may make the ads you see less relevant to your interests.
We may also work with third parties that collect data about your use of the Sites and other sites or apps over time for non-advertising purposes. We use Google Analytics and other third-party services to improve the performance of the Sites and for analytics and marketing purposes. For more information about how Google Analytics collects and uses data when you use our Sites, visit
www.google.com/policies/privacy/partners
, and to opt out of Google Analytics, visit
tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout
.
Additionally, the “help” portion of the toolbar on most browsers will tell you how to prevent your browser from accepting new cookies, how to have the browser notify you when you receive a new cookie, or how to disable cookies altogether. If you use these tools, our Sites may not function as intended.
SESSION RECORDING
We use session recording software provided by FullStory (
www.fullstory.com
) to help us analyze user behavior and improve the user experience on our Sites. This software records user interactions with our Sites, such as mouse movements, clicks, and typing. The data collected by FullStory is used to identify and resolve usability issues and enhance our services.
Data Collected by FullStory:
