Zumba Fitness, LLC is a Florida limited liability company with its principal place of business located at 800 Silks Run, Suite 2310, Hallandale, Florida USA 33009 (“Zumba”, “us,” “we” or “our”). If you are a resident in the European Economic Area ("EEA"), Switzerland, or the United Kingdom, Zumba Fitness, LLC is the responsible party or data controller with respect to Personal Data (defined below) we collect. If you have any questions or concerns at any time, please do not hesitate to contact us at the address above or by contacting us at
privacy@zumba.com
.
This Privacy Policy sets forth our policy with respect to information that we collect from individuals (“Personal Data”) that access or use the Zumba.com website and other websites or apps (e.g., the Zumba Dance Fitness Party App (the “Zumba App”), STRONGNation.com, Zumba-Cruise.com, etc.) that link to this Privacy Policy (the “Sites”). This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and share Personal Data. Provisions of this Privacy Policy may be changed, modified, added or removed at any time and such changes will become effective immediately upon the posting of a new policy on the Sites. This Privacy Policy is incorporated into, and is subject to, our
Terms of Use
.
INFORMATION WE COLLECT?
When using our Sites, you voluntarily supply information about yourself, including your name, image, gender, date of birth, lifestyle choices such as exercise habits, email address, billing address, mailing address, billing information, telephone number, credit card number, credit card expiration date, shipping address, log-in name and password, social network username, calendar, and, with your permission, geolocation information, step counts, and heart rate. For example, we collect this information when you join our email list, create an account, sign up for a class, contact us, or interact with us for any other purpose. We may also collect (i) your mailing and billing information when you place an order with us, such as to purchase apparel, footwear, or accessory products on our Site; and (ii) your health information such as step counts, heart rate, and calories burned if you choose to permit this within the Zumba App (see the Workout Data Transfer to Third Party App section of this Privacy Policy).
We (and other entities) automatically collect certain types of information regarding your interaction with, and use of, our products and services. For example, as is common practice, we use "cookies" and similar technologies to obtain and determine certain information when you access the Sites including, IP address, browser type, and operating system and platform. For users of our mobile services, with your consent, we collect your location when you use the service. We may also receive other information from your mobile device, such as a device identifier, which uniquely identifies your mobile device. See the “Digital Advertising & Analytics” section of this Privacy Policy to learn more about the use of this information and the choices available to you.
We do not knowingly collect Personal Data from children under the age of thirteen (13). If you are a parent or guardian and have reason to believe that a child under the age of 13 has provided Personal Data to us through the Sites, please email us at
privacy@zumba.com
, and we will delete that information from our records.
COOKIES?
Cookies are alphanumeric identifiers that we transfer to your computer's hard drive through your Web browser to enable our systems to recognize your browser and to provide features for using our services. Cookies allow you to take full advantage of some of the features of our services and the Sites, and we recommend that you leave them turned on.
KIND OF COOKIES WE USE?
Cookies come in different varieties and our services may use several of those types. Broadly speaking, we use one or more of the following categories of cookies:
Strictly Necessary Cookies
- These cookies are essential to enable you to navigate the Sites and use their features. Without these cookies, services like the shopping cart cannot be provided.
Performance Cookies
- These cookies collect information about how you use the Sites— for instance, which webpages you go to most. This data may be used to help optimize the Sites and make it easier for you to navigate. These cookies may also be used to let our affiliates know if you came to the Sites from an affiliate and if your visit resulted in the use or purchase of a product or service from us, including details of the product or service purchased.
Functionality Cookies
- These cookies allow us to remember choices you make while browsing. For example, we may store your geographic location in a cookie to ensure that we show you the Sites localized for your area. They may also be used to keep track of what featured products or videos have been viewed to avoid repetition.
Targeting Cookies
- These cookies are used to deliver advertisements more relevant to you and your interests. They are also used to limit the number of times you see an advertisement as well as help measure the effectiveness of the advertising campaign. They are usually placed by advertising networks with our permission.
HOW WE USE PERSONAL DATA
We may use Personal Data for any lawful purpose, including the following:
To register for, and provide you with the products or services you request, including the Zumba® or STRONG Nation® Instructor Training Course;
For identification and authentication purposes across our services to allow you to log in from any location and on any device;
To create a profile for you with the information needed to provide you with our products or services;
To allow you to become and maintain your status as a Licensed Zumba
®
and/or STRONG Nation
®
Instructor, including by communicating with you concerning your license, the status of your license, and your benefits as a licensee;
To send updates, promotions, and marketing materials that may be of interest to you, including carefully selected offers from other businesses;
To operate and improve our products, programs and services;
To operate, personalize and improve the Sites, including for analytics purposes;
To provide customer support, including to respond to your inquiries;
To comply with the law and to maintain the security of our Sites; or
With your consent, or as otherwise disclosed at the time information is collected.
HOW WE SHARE PERSONAL DATA
We may share the information we collect with other parties, including the following:
With our subsidiaries, affiliates, and any joint venture partners that we may have in the future;
With our service providers who assist us in conducting our business, including third parties involved in credit card processing, shipping, data management, email distribution, market research, information analysis, and promotions management;
Upon governmental request, in response to a court order, when required by law, to enforce our policies, or to protect our or others' rights, property or safety;
To prevent illegal uses of our products or services or violations of our Terms of Use, or to defend ourselves against third party claims;
To companies assisting us in fraud protection or investigations;
To a third party as part of our business assets in the event of a sale of all or a portion of our company; and
With your consent or as otherwise disclosed at the time of data collection or sharing.
We may share deidentified information without limitation.
The Sites may offer interactive features, such as the ability to leave reviews, that you can use to communicate with other Site visitors or to submit and post your own content. If you disclose information in one of these forums, this information can be viewed, collected, and used by others.
WORKOUT DATA TRANSFER TO THIRD PARTY APPS
We may share deidentified information without limitation.
Within the Zumba App, users have the option to grant us permission to retrieve workout information, step count, heart rate, and active energy (calories) burned (“Workout Data”) from a user's Apple Health (iOS) or Google Fit/Health Connect account, enabling the display of this Workout Data for your Zumba® classes within the Zumba App.  Certain of this data may be considered biometric data under applicable laws.  If you choose to use the Zumba App during your Zumba® / STRONG Nation® classes, we will write the Workout Data back to Apple Health or Google Fit/Health Connect for a seamless integration of your workout information.
We will not exchange any Workout Data with Apple's Health app or the Google Fit/Health Connect app without your prior approval. Approval is given by you in the relevant settings of the Apple Health app, the Google Fit/Health Connect app, or within the Zumba App during the initial user profile setup or via app settings. You can sync some, all, or none of your Workout Data. You can withdraw your consent at any time in your Zumba App profile by clicking “Support”, then “My Workout Data”, then “Revoke My Workout Data Permissions”. You can delete your Workout Data at any time in your profile by clicking “Support”, then “My Workout Data”, then “Delete My Workout Data”.
Your Workout Data is not shared with any third parties. We store your Workout data on our servers. Your data is encrypted in transit, which means during the transfer from your device to our servers. Access to your data requires authorization. We will retain your Workout Data for up to three (3) years following your last interaction with the Zumba App, or when we no longer need it, whichever is shorter
